description: Bursting at the seams with ideas and mushy emotionality, Cindy Lee's hypnagogic 2-hour magnum opus has quite rightly been touted as one of the best albums of the year - if not the decade. Ex-Women frontperson Patrick Flegel's vision of rock 'n roll is anachronistically nostalgic, an oily tincture of vintage psych, dilated funk and ghosted girl group pop that stews in its heartbreaking sincerity. description:
Chinah's Fine, aka the sampled voice on Two Shell's 'Home', comes correct on her debut solo album, focusing her songwriting and coming up with a deceptively minimal, electronically-enhanced vision of homespun folk-pop - somewhere between Mazzy Star and ML Buch.
